 of records to process.\n\nWhen working with file-based batches, I count the file records and data records during the file layout validation phase that precedes the main processing. For logging, I use the `writeLog` method provided by the batch action parent class. I'm checking for cross-references and external documentation links in the source material, but there aren't any Javadoc references or URLs to include. Since the base URL is empty, the official documentation URLs array will be empty as well. Now I'm moving on to assemble the JSON output with the information I've gathered. me write the section content properly:\n\n```\n## DBをインプットとするバッチの場合\n\n**クラス**: `nablarch.core.db.support.DbAccessSupport`\n\n`countByParameterizedSql` メソッドで処理対象レコード数を取得する。件数取得は `createReader` 内で行う。NablarchはSELECT文をCOUNT取得用のSQL文に書き換えて件数を返す。\n\n```sql\nGET_DELETE_USER_LIST =\nSELECT\n    USER_ID\nFROM\n    SYSTEM_ACCOUNT\nWHERE\n    EFFECTIVE_DATE_TO <= :effectiveDateTo\nORDER BY\n    USER_ID\n```\n\n```java\n// createReader内で件数取得を行う\n```\n\nNow I'm showing how to call `countByParameterizedSql` with different condition types—passing an entity object, a Map, or no conditions at all—to retrieve the record count for batch processing.\n\n## ファイルをインプットとするバッチの場合\n\nMoving on to the file input batch scenario...\n\nWhen laying out the structure, I need to count and retrieve both the file record count and data record count during the layout review phase.\n\n## ログ出力方法\n\nThe batch action's parent class provides a `writeLog` method for outputting logs.\n\nNow I'm parsing the RST document structure to identify the sections and content hierarchy...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":21205,"cache_read_input_tokens":29889,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":21205,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4bbfc174-99ba-468f-a480-0ad6e81ab2ad","